The paper deals with the issue of bias in deep generative models learned on image datasets, specifically the CelebA and CelebA-HQ datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a post-hoc solution to address this issue, which involves utilizing an Ising attribute prior learned in the attribute space. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves face manipulation experiments, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of bias, which suggests that it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
